## Operational Guidance

{% if auth_strategy == "session" %}
- Use Django session auth for admin- or browser-centric internal applications.
{% elif auth_strategy == "jwt" %}
- Use JWT for SPA or machine-consumable APIs and keep token handling centralized.
{% elif auth_strategy == "token" %}
- Use token auth for simple API consumer setups where session auth is not appropriate.
{% elif auth_strategy == "oauth2" %}
- Use OAuth2 when delegated auth or external identity providers are part of the system.
{% else %}
- No authentication is assumed. Confirm that this is a conscious decision before production work starts.
{% endif %}

{% if use_celery %}
- Celery is part of the intended architecture. Keep task orchestration outside request handlers.
{% endif %}
{% if use_channels %}
- Channels support is expected for websocket or asynchronous connection workflows.
{% endif %}

